	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2>Someone related to me that the goblin battlemaster that roams FV at times (not those wimpy Lake BMs ,this guy was whooping me pretty good at 43) is the PH for Hobble, sure nuff, everytime we killed BM, Hobble spawned. Fuzz still runs like a bat out of hell though, and the only way I have found to get him stop long enough to make the switch, aside from root and zone, is to wait just before him ad Hobble engage an enemy. Give him one scale right before he starts fighting, and the trade window will stay open while he fights. Got to be quick though, cause he's liable to take off at any moment. Hope this helps<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr><tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td  align=right valign=bottom><span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr></form></table>
